    "created_at": "2015-08-29T13:51:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-08-29T13:51:08Z",
    "body": "No, my use-case is a hash table database which needs to have more than 1000+ files open by design at times until compaction catches up. I think there is actually an outstanding issue with graceful-fs and Electron in any event.\n\nThe best would be for Electron to just set it to MAX(system limit, 1024).\n"
  },
